Weeks 1–2 — Preprocess THOR-MAGNI first. This is your ground truth backbone. Extract synchronized (RGB-D centroid, LiDAR cluster, velocity GT) triplets at 10Hz (downsampled from 100Hz to keep training tractable). Your regression target is clean here, which makes it ideal for initial training and validation.
Week 3 — Train and validate on THOR-MAGNI only. Hold out 20% of sequences (not frames — sequences, to avoid data leakage across time). Get your baseline MAE against the Kalman filter here before touching the robot.
Week 4 — Collect your 30-min domain adaptation set in the actual deployment environment (hallway, lab, wherever your demo will be). Label it by running your trained model + Kalman filter together and taking Kalman's output as pseudo-labels where the two agree. This avoids needing manual annotation.
Weeks 5–6 — Fine-tune on your collected data with a low learning rate (1e-4 or lower), freezing early layers. This bridges the Orbbec Astra vs. THOR-MAGNI sensor gap, which is the single biggest risk to your demo performing well.
Week 7 — Demo prep. Focus entirely on the A/B comparison (DWA with/without your velocity estimates). RViz2 with velocity arrows will be visually compelling — make sure the arrow scaling is intuitive.
